value.0: Extraordinarily potent scimitar, manufactured by the crafters of Abiz in response to the undead hordes in the now dead city of Abiz. Only bards of epic station may wield it properly, making it sing in its speed and accuracy. When swung its humming drone creates a magical ward for the mind, and its user is immune to silence.
This powerful harp is made on the desert island of Abiz by the minstrel Saraha Zad. A musician of extreme skill can sound three magical chords a day from its 16 strings.

This very small lyre almost looks like a small guitar. Its has a small soundbox at its base made from black balsom wood of Abiz. The instrument itself is nearly weightless but has a smooth sound. A skilled bard can strum three chords of magic.

This eight-stringed masterwork lyre can be played to cast haste, remove curse, and sound burst each once per day.
This odd, curved whistle is made of the hardest metal and inscribed with powerful warding runes. Only skilled bards can make wind of its note. It is manufactured in Abiz.
Musical instruments, some broken and being repaired, line the rack.
Woodworking tools and strings line this rack. Small pieces of fine wood and metal are scattered about its base.

Extraordinarily potent scimitar, manufactured by the crafters of Abiz in response to the undead hordes in the now dead city of Abiz. Only bards of epic station may wield it properly, making it sing in its speed and accuracy. When swung its humming drone creates a magical ward for the mind, and its user is immune to silence.
These magical pipes are made in Abiz in honor of the god Horus-Re. Though they may be played normally at any time, a skilled bard can blow on them to magical effect.
This odd, curved whistle is made of the hardest metal and inscribed with powerful warding runes. Only skilled bards can make wind of its note. It is manufactured in Abiz.

A wise and powerful bard in Trondor named Capar created the first of these instruments. Others have since copied the designs, keeping the name Capar to honor him. This one is made on the island of Abiz.

This pear-shaped masterwork lute can be played to produce cure light wounds, mage armor, and sleep each once per day.
This fairly large harp is heavy, its base it made from melted sands of Abiz. When struck it makes low tones. When struck by a skilled bard, three of its chords produce magical effect.
A small but well-crafted hand-held harp.

This harp has many differently colored strings. Small pictures of scimitars adorn its wood. It is made on the island of Abiz and a skilled musician can bring forth three magical chords.

This masterwork harp can be played to cast mass charm, mass haste, and summon monster VI each once per day.

This small lute is made from the heart of a desert cactus of Abiz. Its tone is lush and full, and a skilled bard can strum three chords of magic.

This pear-shaped masterwork lute can be played to produce ghostly visage, hold person, and neutralize poison each once per day.

This very small lyre almost looks like a small guitar. Its has a small soundbox at its base made from black balsom wood of Abiz. The instrument itself is nearly weightless but has a smooth sound. A skilled bard can strum three chords of magic.

This eight-stringed masterwork lyre can be played to cast haste, remove curse, and sound burst each once per day.

This mandolin is bound in the skin of a blue dragon of Abiz. Its can be struck by a skilled bard to produce three chords of magic.

This eight-stringed masterwork mandolin can be played to cast cure serious wounds, dispel magic, and summon monster III each once per day.
This is an elegantly-crafted mandolin, giving off a faint aura of magic.
This powerful harp is made on the desert island of Abiz by the minstrel Saraha Zad. A musician of extreme skill can sound three magical chords a day from its 16 strings.

This mask is made from ivory and ebony, two toned and handsomely made. Though it can be worn as a stage prop, an actor/bard does not need to wear it constantly to activate its magic. Just placing the mask on the face is all that is needed to draw powerful emotions from those seeing it. Insane humor and moaning death can be brought forth by its magic. It is constructed by the skilled crafters of Abiz but con only be activated by the most skilled of bards.
